---
import MainLayout from "../../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import MotuSidebar from '../../../components/MotuSidebar.astro';

const title = "Low-latency Monitoring — UltraLite-mk3";
const description = "Direct monitoring and buffer settings.";
---

<MainLayout title={title} description={description}>
    <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
      <div class="w-[250px] flex-shrink-0">
        <MotuSidebar />
      </div>
      <article class="prose max-w-none">
      <h1>Monitoring &amp; Headphones</h1>

      <h2>Main Output → HS7 Monitors</h2>
      <p>Assign <strong>CueMix FX Mix 1</strong> to the Main Outputs (channels 1/2) and connect those to the Yamaha HS7 monitors with balanced TRS cables. The Mix 1 main output represents the studio reference monitoring environment — keep it flat and accurate.</p>

      <h2>Headphone Monitoring</h2>
      <p>The front-panel headphone output has its own dedicated volume knob, independent from the main output level. Assign a separate CueMix FX mix bus (e.g. Mix 2) to the headphone output for a completely different balance than what the monitors hear.</p>

      <h2>Zero-Latency Vocal Monitoring Chain</h2>
      <p>This is the optimal recording chain for tracking vocals through the SM58:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>SM58 → MOTU input 1 (XLR, mic preamp, +48V OFF).</li>
        <li>In CueMix FX, create a direct send from Input 1 → Mix 2 (headphone bus). No computer involved in this path.</li>
        <li>Add Classic Reverb send in Mix 2 for vocal comfort monitoring (keep the reverb only in the headphone mix, not Mix 1).</li>
        <li>In Ableton, set the vocal Audio Track Monitor to <strong>Off</strong> (prevents software-path doubling with the CueMix direct monitor).</li>
        <li>Vocalist hears their own voice with zero added latency through headphones connected to the front-panel PHONES jack.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Multiple Cue Mix Management</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Mix 1 (Main/Studio monitors):</strong> flat, accurate, everything at session balance. What goes to the HS7s.</li>
        <li><strong>Mix 2 (Headphone cue):</strong> vocalist's headphone mix. SM58 input +6 dB relative to the backing track, reverb send active, everything else at normal level.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Both mixes can be configured and saved simultaneously in CueMix FX — no need to reconfigure when switching between studio listening and recorded tracking.</p>

      <img src="https://cdn-data.motu.com/site/images/ultralite-mk3/hybrid-sm.png" alt="Hybrid" class="w-36 inline-block mr-4" />
    </article>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
